[2
Date: Sat, 9 Jan 1999 15:46:54 CAT
From: Mary-Lou Penrith <marylou@moon.ovi.ac.za>

In response to your report of 8 January: we have heard that African swine
fever has been confirmed in Madagascar by a laboratory in France. There is
no vaccine and no treatment for this disease. The only known way to control
it is by slaughter of all infected and in-contact pigs, but doing this
without compensation does tend to
encourage spread of the disease by clandestine movements of pigs and pork.
Recent experiences in West Africa with this disease have been rather
discouraging.
We will be interested to receive any further reports of the situation in
Madagascar.
--
Mary-Louise Penrith
ARC-Onderstepoort Veterinary Institute
Onderstepoort
South Africa
e-mail: marylou@moon.ovi.ac.za
